The paper discusses a calibration method for industrial robots and laser range finders, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of geometric planar constraints and optimization algorithms suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also mentions the importance of accuracy in various applications, indicating a potential connection to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of simulations suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) for visualization and testing purposes.
